parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to not start, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks, such as being stranded in traffic or in remote areas. Additionally, electrical malfunctions can lead to fires or other hazards.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the ignition switch is hot or smoking
electrical devices malfunction or become inoperative
accessories such as the air conditioner
windshield wipers
and radio do not function
the starter relay fails
and the alternator fails
causing the vehicle to stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the belt may not restrain the driver or passenger properly.
symptoms: The seat belt does not move forward
the seat belt motor has stopped working
the seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt fails to restrain the driver or passenger
the seat belt locks when retracted
the seat belt buckle intermittently will not latch.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Acceleration due to Cruise Control Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, posing a significant risk to the safety of the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates or jumps forward
often when parking or driving
resulting in loss of control
crashes
or near-miss incidents.
